Function Reference/submit button « WordPress Codex
-----------

Echos a submit button, with provided text and appropriate class

Usage
-----

` <?php submit_button( $text, $type, $name, $wrap, $other_attributes ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$text` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The text of the button (defaults to 'Save Changes')
    Default:

 `$type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The type of button. One of: primary, secondary, delete
    Default: 'primary'

 `$name` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The
    [HTML](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML "wikipedia:HTML") name of
    the submit button. Defaults to "submit". If no id attribute is given
    in `$other_attributes` below, `$name` will be used as the button's
    id.
    Default: 'submit'

 `$wrap` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) True if the output button should be wrapped in a
    paragraph tag, false otherwise. Defaults to true
    Default: true

 `$other_attributes` 
:   ([*array|string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Array.7Cstring "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*NULL*) optional
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

echos an html submit button.

